text:
Greene Street, east side, south across Houston Street towards Prince Street.
September 26, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

Houston Street, south side, west from and including No. 55 West, between Greene and Wooster Streets. Demolition of No. 69, west of Wooster Street, is going on. The whole south side, as shown here, is about to be razed.

September 19, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

151, 153-157 Greene Street, at and adjoining the N.W. corner of Houston Street, seen from the vacant S.E. corner. The buildings on the south side of Houston Street (q.v.), from Broadway to Sixth Avenue, were all cleared away late in 1929.
February 21, 1932.

P. L. Sperr.

Shacks of unemployed squatters on Houston Street, south side, east of Greene Street.
